rComments: Decent prof and a decent course. There's a lot of work and effort that needs to be put into his courses, and sometimes his expectations are unclear unless you really press him for feedback. But, overall, his courses are enjoyable.

Printmaking classes are extremely hard in process, however very rewarding. Hawken does have high expectations. He is very helpful and knowledgeable. Like any professor, he should be approached first. Very understanding and does not waste your time.
He is a nice person but dont expect high grades if you'r not good with drawing or not creative, he has high expectations.

Don't expect to learn how to draw well from one of his courses. In fact, don't even expect much feedback period unless you press him for it. Some here have called him engaging when he's not even technically a 'teacher' to his students.
Awesome and engaging instructor who is extremely knowledgable and approachable.
It looks easy, but the actual practice of it is hard.
